#Text=As regards the application of the Hustler v. Falwell case to this case , I think the overall application was fair : Parody and satire are protected forms of free speech .

#Text=( ( WN ) ) On September 29 , 2009 , your lawyer Marc Randazza requested that Glenn Beck agree to stipulate to the application of the United States Constitution , and also especially to the First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution . In an October 19 interview with Wikinews , Randazza said that Beck had not responded to this request . Why do you think Beck chose not to stipulate to the U.S. Constitution and the First Amendment in this case ?
#Text=E-H :
#Text=I think Beck knew that doing so would hurt his case .
#Text=The rights of free speech we enjoy in the United States are broader than in some other countries .
#Text=WIPO , being an international organization , could well have assigned an arbitrator from a country that does n't protect speech as strongly as we do .
#Text=And WIPO , not being bound by the U.S. Constitution , might not choose to consider the strong protections we have in rendering their decision .

#Text=We also felt it was ironic that Glenn Beck , who is on record as being against an international body making judgments that might overrule the U.S. Constitution , would himself choose to use an international body to try and stifle speech that would be protected under the U.S. Constitution .
#Text=So ultimately , you could say we were trying to help him retain the patriotic image he has worked to hard to present .
#Text=Ultimately , the arbitrator applied the First Amendment anyhow .
#Text=We felt that in sending that letter , we would give Beck a chance to show that his purported support for the constitution was real .
#Text=His failure to respond shows everyone that he is full of shit .

#Text=We also felt it was ironic that Glenn Beck , who is on record as being against an international body making judgments that might overrule the U.S. Constitution , would himself choose to use an international body to try and stifle speech that would be protected under the U.S. Constitution . — Eiland-Hall

#Text=( ( WN ) ) An article in Online Media Daily noted , the decision in your WIPO case , " appears to mark a significant win for digital rights advocates because a ruling in Beck 's favor could have encouraged other subjects of online parodies to take their complaints directly to the WIPO rather than U.S. courts , which are bound by the First Amendment . " How do you feel about the fact that your case may have set precedent for similar cases in the future ?
#Text=E-H : If this has truly set precedent , I am honored to have the chance to serve the cause of Liberty .
#Text=I 'm nobody special , mind you .
#Text=Anyone could have set up a site - it just happened to be me that got thrown in the center of this fight .
